sql:
SELECT label
FROM medical_terms
WHERE term_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT term_id) AS total_unique_terms
FROM access_logs
WHERE user_id = 0 AND access_type = 'edit';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT term_id) 
FROM medical_terms 
WHERE created_by = 2;

SELECT COUNT(term_id) AS usage_count
FROM term_usages
WHERE term_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'Clinicians' refers to users with the role of 'clinician'; 
- 'Surgery Department' is one of the possible department names a user can belong to; 
- 'Most frequently accessed' refers to the highest count of access events.
